/**
 * ============================================================
 *  Owner: Taisei (UI & Component Layer)
 *  File: TaskCard component (a single task card)
 * ============================================================
 *
 *  【What to do】
 *  Design the visual template for a task card.
 *  NOTE: Cards are created dynamically at runtime by JavaScript,
 *  so this file serves as a DESIGN REFERENCE and HTML/CSS template.
 *  Suzuna's KanbanBoard.ts will create card elements using this structure.
 *
 *  【Card HTML structure to follow】
 *  <div class="task-card" draggable="true" data-task-id="{id}">
 *    <h3 class="task-title">{title}</h3>
 *    <p class="task-due-date">{dueDate}</p>
 *  </div>
 *
 *  【Important attributes for Carlos】
 *  - draggable="true"     → enables HTML5 drag & drop
 *  - data-task-id="{id}"  → used to identify which task is being dragged
 *  - class="task-card"    → Carlos uses this to attach drag event listeners
 *
 *  【Click behavior】
 *  - Clicking a card should open the View Task modal
 *    (Carlos will attach the click event listener in modal.ts)
 *
 *  【Design tips】
 *  - Keep cards compact: show title + due date only
 *  - Add hover effect and cursor: grab for drag affordance
 *  - While dragging: reduce opacity (Carlos handles this in dragAndDrop.ts)
 * ============================================================
 */
---

<!-- This is a static preview / design reference for the task card -->
